  "texts": [
    "In this -VAE method, the authors mention that the data generation of VAEs is often referred to as learning a disentangled representation of the latent space, as latent units are sensitive to one generative factor, but insensitive to other factors, that is, the insight for a generative VAE considered disentangled VAE (Burgess et al. 2018).",
    "In Fig. 3, handwritten digits generated using the basic VAE and -VAE methods are shown.",
    "The digits look like a mixture of many other digits, proving that a VAE interpolates the latent space.",
    "Furthermore, the basic VAE also generates unrealistic-looking digits, which shows its entangled nature, whereas the -VAE generates more realistic digits by disentangling the latent space.",
    "(5) z = + Fig. 2 The architecture of the VAE model."
  ]
